						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Agastyēśvara shrine, Agastyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 4: 975 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Much damaged. It seems to record a gift of ten <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēva of Avanigandharva-Īśvara-gṛiham, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉam</hi> in Kuṉṟa-kkūṟṟam by Atiśūraṉ •••• of Maḻapāḍi in [Vā]ṇagoppāḍi. He deposited the amount with two <hi rend="italic">nagarattār</hi> each with five <hi rend="italic">poṉ.</hi> The inscription also refers to a later order, the nature of which is not known, of Aḍigaḷ Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar Kaṇḍaṉ [Amuda]nār made in the [13]th year of Uttamachōḻa, evidently about the utilization of this amount.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 105.</p>						

						</summary>
